{"id":"d=origam-topic-3918//p=ee841d52a9f742ac96bc7f14c4b4dc1c","tags":{"__document_id":["origam-topic-3918"],"__file_type":["text/plain"],"__file_id":["f274789c25474af88a911ee4235cbeec"],"__file_part":["9ed22b8da09d4f33a27dbf502f9628f3"],"__part_n":["1"],"__sect_n":["0"],"source":["origam-community"],"category":["docs"],"categoryId":["8"],"topicId":["3918"],"url":["https://community.origam.com/t/how-to-view-the-application-database/3918"],"title":["How to view the application database"]},"payload":{"url":"","schema":"20231218A","file":"content.txt","text":" in the Community Edition. You can install a desktop app on your computer or use a web interface by running it in a Docker container. \n To run CloudBeaver \u2013 the version in a Docker container with a browser interface \u2013 run the following command in your terminal: \n  docker run -d -p 8080:8978 --name dbeaver dbeaver/cloudbeaver  \n This will create and start a container named \u201Cdbeaver\u201D with CloudBeaver running inside it. \n Then go to localhost:8080 in your browser and configure your server: \n          CloudBeaver server configuration  2921\u00D71236 254 KB         \n After that, you can connect to your database server: \n          CloudBeaver DB connection configuration  2907\u00D71136 203 KB         \n Please note that you need to address the DB Server (host) by its IP address, as using localhost with a port will probably not work in this scenario. \n To get the DB Server IP address, run the following command: \n  docker inspect container_name  (container_name = name of your container with the DB Server) \n Any issues, you can consult with your favourite AI advisor   \n\n---\n\n@vikter (2025-09-23 07:46:00Z):\n Another option is using Visual Studio Code and the DB Code Database Management Plugin: \n          image  1466\u00D7306 38 KB         \n          image  2936\u00D71794 455 KB         \n In VS Code you can manage also Docker containers and do a lot of other things, and it is for free."